WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:31.800 align:middle line:90%


00:00:31.800 --> 00:00:34.930 align:middle line:84%
Hello, and welcome to
"Awakening the Dreamer,

00:00:34.930 --> 00:00:37.120 align:middle line:90%
Changing the Dream."

00:00:37.120 --> 00:00:41.460 align:middle line:10%
I'm Lynne Twist, the co-founder
of the Pachamama Alliance,

00:00:41.460 --> 00:00:45.520 align:middle line:10%
the organization responsible for
developing this unique program.

00:00:45.520 --> 00:00:48.400 align:middle line:84%
The word "pachamama"
comes from South America,

00:00:48.400 --> 00:00:51.090 align:middle line:84%
from the Quechua people of
the Amazon and the Andes,

00:00:51.090 --> 00:00:54.840 align:middle line:84%
where "pachamama"
means "Mother Earth"--

00:00:54.840 --> 00:00:58.100 align:middle line:84%
or more completely to
them, the earth, the sky,

00:00:58.100 --> 00:01:01.300 align:middle line:90%
the universe, and all time.

00:01:01.300 --> 00:01:03.570 align:middle line:84%
First, let me thank you
for being someone who cares

00:01:03.570 --> 00:01:06.100 align:middle line:84%
enough about our precious
planet and the human family

00:01:06.100 --> 00:01:10.580 align:middle line:84%
to take the time to participate
in this important program.

00:01:10.580 --> 00:01:14.290 align:middle line:84%
I guarantee that you'll
be really glad you did.

00:01:14.290 --> 00:01:17.730 align:middle line:84%
We're living in amazing times,
as you may have noticed.

00:01:17.730 --> 00:01:21.120 align:middle line:84%
So much is changing
around us all the time.

00:01:21.120 --> 00:01:23.860 align:middle line:84%
Some extraordinary
changes are for the good.

00:01:23.860 --> 00:01:27.220 align:middle line:84%
But some bring up real
fears about the future.

00:01:27.220 --> 00:01:29.510 align:middle line:84%
And so you may find yourself
worrying about the state

00:01:29.510 --> 00:01:31.210 align:middle line:84%
of the world and
questioning if there's

00:01:31.210 --> 00:01:33.630 align:middle line:90%
anything you can do about it.

00:01:33.630 --> 00:01:35.630 align:middle line:84%
This experience
you're taking part in

00:01:35.630 --> 00:01:40.150 align:middle line:84%
is about both the urgency and
the opportunity of our times.

00:01:40.150 --> 00:01:44.790 align:middle line:10%
As we will see, humanity is on
an entirely unsustainable path.

00:01:44.790 --> 00:01:48.110 align:middle line:84%
And we have a limited time
to turn things around.

00:01:48.110 --> 00:01:50.550 align:middle line:10%
But you'll also discover
something unexpected

00:01:50.550 --> 00:01:52.890 align:middle line:10%
and profoundly inspiring.

00:01:52.890 --> 00:01:56.250 align:middle line:84%
And that is that the resources
and technologies to address

00:01:56.250 --> 00:01:59.770 align:middle line:90%
this crisis already exist.

00:01:59.770 --> 00:02:02.090 align:middle line:84%
Many experts say
that what is missing

00:02:02.090 --> 00:02:04.860 align:middle line:84%
is the will to implement
the solutions--

00:02:04.860 --> 00:02:07.490 align:middle line:84%
the human commitment
to make it happen.

00:02:07.490 --> 00:02:10.350 align:middle line:84%
This experience is an
opportunity for you to wake

00:02:10.350 --> 00:02:13.970 align:middle line:84%
up to your own role in
creating a new future--

00:02:13.970 --> 00:02:16.800 align:middle line:84%
your part in generating
the collective will

00:02:16.800 --> 00:02:20.810 align:middle line:84%
needed to set us on a
path to a thriving, just,

00:02:20.810 --> 00:02:24.490 align:middle line:84%
and sustainable way
of life for all.

00:02:24.490 --> 00:02:26.240 align:middle line:84%
The "Awakening the Dreamer,
Changing the Dream"

00:02:26.240 --> 00:02:28.810 align:middle line:84%
Program was born out
of a relationship

00:02:28.810 --> 00:02:31.290 align:middle line:84%
between the Pachamama
Alliance and indigenous people

00:02:31.290 --> 00:02:32.345 align:middle line:90%
of the Amazon rain forest.

00:02:32.345 --> 00:02:55.047 align:middle line:90%


00:02:55.047 --> 00:02:56.280 align:middle line:84%
FEMALE NARRATOR:
These are the Achuar

00:02:56.280 --> 00:03:01.650 align:middle line:84%
people, one of our planet's
most remote indigenous groups.

00:03:01.650 --> 00:03:03.870 align:middle line:84%
The Achuar are an
ancient dream culture,

00:03:03.870 --> 00:03:07.450 align:middle line:84%
still living in harmony
with their ancestral land--

00:03:07.450 --> 00:03:10.740 align:middle line:84%
nearly two million acres
of pristine tropical rain

00:03:10.740 --> 00:03:12.657 align:middle line:90%
forest in Ecuador and Peru.

00:03:12.657 --> 00:03:15.580 align:middle line:90%


00:03:15.580 --> 00:03:19.120 align:middle line:84%
In the late 1980s, the
Achuar elders and shamans

00:03:19.120 --> 00:03:22.870 align:middle line:84%
began having dreams and
visions that a grave threat

00:03:22.870 --> 00:03:26.250 align:middle line:90%
was coming to their people.

00:03:26.250 --> 00:03:30.440 align:middle line:10%
The Achuar soon realised what
that threat was as they began

00:03:30.440 --> 00:03:34.020 align:middle line:10%
to see what contact with the
outside world and its thirst

00:03:34.020 --> 00:03:37.030 align:middle line:10%
for oil was doing to
the land and cultures

00:03:37.030 --> 00:03:38.465 align:middle line:10%
of their indigenous neighbors.

00:03:38.465 --> 00:03:41.140 align:middle line:90%


00:03:41.140 --> 00:03:44.320 align:middle line:84%
And so, the Achuar
made a bold move.

00:03:44.320 --> 00:03:46.780 align:middle line:84%
They reached out to
create a partnership

00:03:46.780 --> 00:03:51.320 align:middle line:84%
with the very world that was
threatening to destroy them.

00:03:51.320 --> 00:03:54.300 align:middle line:84%
MALE NARRATOR: In 1995,
a call issued forth

00:03:54.300 --> 00:03:56.630 align:middle line:84%
from the heart of the
natural world that was heard

00:03:56.630 --> 00:03:58.930 align:middle line:84%
thousands of miles
away by a small group

00:03:58.930 --> 00:04:01.530 align:middle line:90%
of people in the modern world.

00:04:01.530 --> 00:04:04.020 align:middle line:84%
In the summer of that
year in a remote village

00:04:04.020 --> 00:04:07.740 align:middle line:84%
in the rain forest, these
two worlds came together.

00:04:07.740 --> 00:04:09.910 align:middle line:84%
And the Pachamama
Alliance was born.

00:04:09.910 --> 00:04:14.780 align:middle line:90%


00:04:14.780 --> 00:04:17.040 align:middle line:10%
From the very beginning,
our indigenous partners

00:04:17.040 --> 00:04:18.980 align:middle line:10%
told us that it was
really, really great

00:04:18.980 --> 00:04:20.649 align:middle line:10%
that we were working
with them in the Amazon,

00:04:20.649 --> 00:04:22.180 align:middle line:10%
shoulder to shoulder.

00:04:22.180 --> 00:04:24.450 align:middle line:10%
But that was only
half the battle.

00:04:24.450 --> 00:04:27.090 align:middle line:10%
They told us that if we really
wanted to protect their lands

00:04:27.090 --> 00:04:29.980 align:middle line:10%
permanently, we would
need to go to work

00:04:29.980 --> 00:04:32.110 align:middle line:10%
in our part of the world.

00:04:32.110 --> 00:04:34.290 align:middle line:84%
And as they put
it, we would need

00:04:34.290 --> 00:04:37.110 align:middle line:84%
to change the dream
of the North--

00:04:37.110 --> 00:04:41.860 align:middle line:84%
the dream of the modern world--
a dream rooted in consumption

00:04:41.860 --> 00:04:45.350 align:middle line:84%
and acquisition without any
regard to the consequences

00:04:45.350 --> 00:04:48.920 align:middle line:84%
to the natural world
or even our own future.

00:04:48.920 --> 00:04:51.010 align:middle line:10%
Changing the dream
of the modern world

00:04:51.010 --> 00:04:53.130 align:middle line:10%
is certainly a
daunting-- and some would

00:04:53.130 --> 00:04:55.300 align:middle line:10%
even say an impossible-- task.

00:04:55.300 --> 00:04:59.370 align:middle line:10%
But we took the request of
the Achuar very seriously.

00:04:59.370 --> 00:05:01.600 align:middle line:10%
Out of our work
with them, we came

00:05:01.600 --> 00:05:03.750 align:middle line:10%
to see that we in
the modern world

00:05:03.750 --> 00:05:08.290 align:middle line:10%
truly are in some kind of a
trance-- living in a dream

00:05:08.290 --> 00:05:10.580 align:middle line:10%
that's threatening to
destroy not only the rain

00:05:10.580 --> 00:05:14.320 align:middle line:10%
forest and their way of life
but the health and well-being

00:05:14.320 --> 00:05:16.370 align:middle line:10%
of our entire planet.

00:05:16.370 --> 00:05:20.440 align:middle line:84%
Our society is on a
completely unsustainable path.

00:05:20.440 --> 00:05:22.690 align:middle line:84%
And experts
everywhere are saying

00:05:22.690 --> 00:05:25.524 align:middle line:84%
that we have a limited
time to turn things around.

00:05:25.524 --> 00:05:33.330 align:middle line:90%


00:05:33.330 --> 00:05:34.830 align:middle line:10%
MALE NARRATOR: So in
response to the requests

00:05:34.830 --> 00:05:36.790 align:middle line:10%
that came from its
indigenous partners,

00:05:36.790 --> 00:05:39.870 align:middle line:10%
the Pachamama Alliance
created this symposium,

00:05:39.870 --> 00:05:43.440 align:middle line:10%
"Awakening the Dreamer, Changing
the Dream"-- now being offered

00:05:43.440 --> 00:05:45.400 align:middle line:10%
by thousands of
volunteers in dozens

00:05:45.400 --> 00:05:46.885 align:middle line:10%
of countries around the world.

00:05:46.885 --> 00:05:50.790 align:middle line:90%


00:05:50.790 --> 00:05:53.930 align:middle line:84%
The purpose of this symposium
is an audacious one-- bringing

00:05:53.930 --> 00:05:56.290 align:middle line:84%
forth an environmentally
sustainable,

00:05:56.290 --> 00:05:58.630 align:middle line:84%
spiritually fulfilling,
socially just

00:05:58.630 --> 00:06:00.465 align:middle line:90%
human presence on this planet.

00:06:00.465 --> 00:06:04.920 align:middle line:90%


00:06:04.920 --> 00:06:07.450 align:middle line:10%
FEMALE NARRATOR: The intention
is that by the end-- rather

00:06:07.450 --> 00:06:10.380 align:middle line:10%
than seeing these as
three separate issues--

00:06:10.380 --> 00:06:13.910 align:middle line:10%
you see them as
interrelated facets of one

00:06:13.910 --> 00:06:17.630 align:middle line:10%
profoundly
interconnected whole--

00:06:17.630 --> 00:06:20.750 align:middle line:10%
and that you not only
understand the scope and urgency

00:06:20.750 --> 00:06:23.520 align:middle line:10%
of the planetary
situation we face,

00:06:23.520 --> 00:06:26.800 align:middle line:10%
but you also see that the
possibility of our times

00:06:26.800 --> 00:06:28.498 align:middle line:10%
is greater than the crisis.

00:06:28.498 --> 00:06:33.940 align:middle line:90%


00:06:33.940 --> 00:06:37.070 align:middle line:84%
The goal is that you leave
here in a state that could

00:06:37.070 --> 00:06:40.570 align:middle line:90%
be described as blessed unrest.

00:06:40.570 --> 00:06:43.950 align:middle line:10%
The main purpose of the
"Awakening Dream" or program

00:06:43.950 --> 00:06:47.630 align:middle line:10%
is to create a cadre
of global citizens

00:06:47.630 --> 00:06:51.410 align:middle line:10%
that are awake-- people who
are engaged in the conversation

00:06:51.410 --> 00:06:54.790 align:middle line:10%
of what's it going to take
to create a new future--

00:06:54.790 --> 00:06:58.840 align:middle line:10%
and that also have the ability
to see that the future is not

00:06:58.840 --> 00:07:00.010 align:middle line:10%
something that's
just we're going

00:07:00.010 --> 00:07:04.190 align:middle line:10%
to live into but it's something
that we can actually create.

00:07:04.190 --> 00:07:06.150 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:07:06.150 --> 00:07:08.600 align:middle line:90%


00:07:08.600 --> 00:07:10.500 align:middle line:10%
MALE NARRATOR: Indigenous
cultures throughout the world

00:07:10.500 --> 00:07:12.690 align:middle line:10%
have legends and
prophesies that identify

00:07:12.690 --> 00:07:17.670 align:middle line:10%
this time we are living in as
a turning point for humanity.

00:07:17.670 --> 00:07:19.760 align:middle line:84%
One such legend is
found throughout much

00:07:19.760 --> 00:07:25.010 align:middle line:84%
of the Americas-- the prophecy
of the eagle and the condor.

00:07:25.010 --> 00:07:26.680 align:middle line:84%
FEMALE NARRATOR: According
to this prophecy,

00:07:26.680 --> 00:07:29.820 align:middle line:84%
the eagle is the bird that
represents cultures that have

00:07:29.820 --> 00:07:33.650 align:middle line:84%
used the creativity of the
mind and scientific insight

00:07:33.650 --> 00:07:36.310 align:middle line:84%
to harness the
wonders of technology

00:07:36.310 --> 00:07:39.510 align:middle line:90%
and increase material wealth.

00:07:39.510 --> 00:07:42.420 align:middle line:84%
The condor represents
more spiritually-oriented

00:07:42.420 --> 00:07:45.310 align:middle line:84%
societies-- those that
are deeply in touch

00:07:45.310 --> 00:07:47.950 align:middle line:84%
with the sacredness
of the natural world

00:07:47.950 --> 00:07:52.450 align:middle line:84%
and the interconnectedness
of all things.

00:07:52.450 --> 00:07:57.530 align:middle line:10%
This legend said that every
500 years, we go through cycles.

00:07:57.530 --> 00:08:00.570 align:middle line:10%
And the last cycle began
at the end of the 1400s,

00:08:00.570 --> 00:08:02.460 align:middle line:10%
roughly the time of Columbus.

00:08:02.460 --> 00:08:04.840 align:middle line:84%
And it was predicted
that during that cycle,

00:08:04.840 --> 00:08:07.460 align:middle line:90%
the eagle would dominate.

00:08:07.460 --> 00:08:10.940 align:middle line:84%
But within 500 years, that
cycle would start to change.

00:08:10.940 --> 00:08:12.280 align:middle line:84%
And the eagle and
the condor would

00:08:12.280 --> 00:08:15.940 align:middle line:84%
fly together in the same skies.
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:08:15.940 --> 00:08:41.221 align:middle line:90%


00:08:41.221 --> 00:08:41.921 align:middle line:90%
